+    After deallocation ops are inserted, this pass simulates tensor
+    lifetimes using a first-fit freelist allocator to detect both classic
+    budget overflows *and* fragmentation-induced OOMs — cases where total
+    free DRAM is sufficient but no single contiguous block large enough for
+    the requested tensor can be found (the real failure mode for Mochi 10B
+    at seq_len=2080 on 4-chip SPMD TP; see GH #11).
+
+    For each Value produced by an op the allocator does a first-fit search
+    over current free ranges (sorted by base address).  On DeallocateOp the
+    range is returned and adjacent ranges merged.  All sizes are rounded up
+    to DRAM_ALIGNMENT (32 bytes) to match tt-metal's L1_ALIGNMENT.
+
+    For TP-sharded (SPMD) models, tensor shapes in the IR already reflect
+    per-chip sizes after SPMD sharding, so a single freelist with the
+    single-chip DRAM budget is sufficient.
+
+    Two diagnostic levels: ERROR when an allocation fails (fragmentation or
+    total OOM); WARNING at 90% utilisation as an early signal.
   }];
 }

