+
+/// Returns the total DRAM bytes consumed by `value` when it is live in device
+/// DRAM.  Returns 0 for non-DRAM tensors (L1, host memory, etc.).
 //
-// For interleaved DRAM (virtual grid N×M, data spread across DRAM channels):
-//   totalBytes = shardSizeBytes × gridVolume (= whole tensor before sharding)
-// For sharded DRAM (N×M physical shards, each on a different set of cores):
-//   totalBytes = shardSizeBytes × gridVolume (= whole tensor)
+// Both DRAM interleaved and DRAM sharded layouts satisfy:
+//   totalBytes = getShardSizeInBytes() × getGridVolume()
